<p style="text-align: left;">
 
<span style="font-size: 25px;"><strong>1976-08-08 &#8211; Big Thompson Flood Help Notice &#8211; Page 1</strong></span>


<br>
A pamphlet distributed days after the July 31st 1976 Big Thompson Flood, providing information on coming help.

<br>
<br>
<span style="font-size: 20px;"><i><strong>Transcription</strong></i></span> 

<br>
<span style="font-size: 22px;"><i>DO YOU NEED HELP?</i></span> 


<br>
<i>"IF YOU HAVE NOT REGISTERED FOR ASSISTANCE AT ONE OF THE ONE-STOP CENTERS, A HELICOPTER WILL MAKE SEVER STOPS ALONG THE CANYON ON SUNDAY, AUG. 8, BRINGING FEDERAL, STATE, AND RED CROSS REPRESENTATIVES WHO MAY BE ABLE TO ASSIST YOU."</i>




<br>
<span style="font-size: 20px;"><i><strong>Details</strong></i></span> 


<br>
<i>Date: 1976-08-08</i>


<br>
<i>Location: USA, Colorado, Loveland, Idlewild</i>




<br>
<i>Source: Dauth Family Archive</i>


<br>


<i>Permalink:</i>
<a href="https://www.idlewildlodge.org/document/1976-08-08-big-thompson-flood-help-notice-page-1/">https://www.idlewildlodge.org/document/1976-08-08-big-thompson-flood-help-notice-page-1/</a>



</p>
<p>
