</div></div></div></div></div></div><script id="script-row-unique-2" data-row="script-row-unique-2" type="text/javascript" class="vc_controls">UNCODE.initRow(document.getElementById("row-unique-2"));</script></div></div></div><div data-parent="true" class="vc_row row-container" id="row-unique-3"><div class="row limit-width row-parent"><div class="wpb_row row-inner"><div class="wpb_column pos-top pos-center align_left column_parent col-lg-12 single-internal-gutter"><div class="uncol style-light"  ><div class="uncoltable"><div class="uncell no-block-padding" ><div class="uncont"><div class="uncode_text_column text-lead" ></p>
<p style="text-align: left;">
 
<span style="font-size: 25px;"><strong>1976-08-08 &#8211; Big Thompson Flood Help Notice &#8211; Page 2</strong></span>


<br>
A pamphlet distributed days after the July 31st 1976 Big Thompson Flood, providing information on coming help.

<br>
<br>
<span style="font-size: 20px;"><i><strong>Transcription</strong></i></span> 



<br>
<i>"YOU WILL BE ABLE TO GET INFORMATION AND ASSISTANCE. 1. FOOD, CLOTHING, IMMEDIATE NEEDS – RED CROSS AID, 2. TEMPORARY HOUSING – DEPARTMENT OF HOUSING AND URBAN DEVELOPMENT, 3. DISASTER LOANS FOR REBUILDING HOMES AND FOR PERSONAL PROPERTY- SMALL BUSINESS ADMINISTRATION, 4. FOOD STAMPS-LARIMER COUNT DEPARTMENT OF SOCIAL SERVICES, 5. GRANT UP TO $5000 FOR NECESSARY EXPENSES AND SERIOUS NEEDS- LARIMER COUNTY DEPARTMENT OF SOCIAL SERVICES, 6. TAX INFORMATION ON CASUALTY LOSSES-INTERNAL REVENUE SERVICE
THE MOBILE TEAM WILL LEAVE LOVELAND AT ABOUT 9:15 AM, AND WILL TRAVEL ALONG U.S. 34, STOPPING AT THE FOLLOWING LOCATIONS: CEDAR COVE, GLEN COVE, DRAKE, WALTONIA, AND OTHER PLACES IN THE CANYON. WHEN YOU HEAR THE HELICOPTERS, COME AND SEE WHAT ASSISTANCE IS AVAILABLE FOR YOUR PARTICULAR DISASTER NEEDS. PLEASE, TELL YOUR NEIGHBORS. REMEMBER, SUNDAY, -FEDERAL DISASTER ASSISTANCE ADMINISTRATION
"</i>




<br>
<span style="font-size: 20px;"><i><strong>Details</strong></i></span> 


<br>
<i>Date: 1976-08-08</i>


<br>
<i>Location: USA, Colorado, Loveland, Idlewild</i>




<br>
<i>Source: Dauth Family Archive</i>


<br>


<i>Permalink:</i>
<a href="https://www.idlewildlodge.org/document/1976-08-08-big-thompson-flood-help-notice-page-2/">https://www.idlewildlodge.org/document/1976-08-08-big-thompson-flood-help-notice-page-2/</a>



</p>
<p>
